							<h2>Training Command</h2>
							<p>Training Command was formed on 22 Jul 1949 with an aim to impart training through
							 training institutes. Training Command traces out its lineage from the No.2 Training Group
							  which was set up immediately after Independence. Training Group was redesignated as 
							  Training Command in 1949. On 15 Aug 1947, the Air Force Training Establishments located 
							  in India were: (a) Initial Training Wing, Coimbatore formed on 11 Jul 46. (b) Elementary
							   Flying Training School, Jodhpur formed on Jul 42. (c) Advanced Flying Training School,
							    Ambala formed on Jul 41. (d) No.1 Ground Training School, Jalahalli formed on Jul 47.
									 (e) No.2 Ground Training School, Tamabaram formed on Feb 47 No.2 (Indian) Group 
									 RAF located at Bangalore.</p>
